pert_summary: Phenytoin (Lepitoin; NSC 8722; Phenytek; Phenytoine; Sodanton; Zentropi) is an inactive voltage-gated sodium channel stabilizer.
Acebutolol is a β-adrenergic receptors antagonist used in the treatment of hypertension, angina pectoris and cardiac arrhythmias.
Acemetacin (Emflex) is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug and a glycolic acid ester of indometacin that is a cyclooxygenase inhibitor.
Alfuzosin(Uroxatral) is an alpha1 receptor antagonist used to treat benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH).
Amiodarone HCl is an antiarrhythmic drug for inhibition of ATP-sensitive potassium channel with IC50 of 19.1 μM.
Amisulpride is an atypical antipsychotic used to treat psychosis in schizophrenia and episodes of mania in bipolar disorder.
Ampiroxicam is a nonselective cyclooxygenase inhibitor uesd as anti-inflammatory drug.
Anastrozole inhibits the enzyme aromatase.
Betahistine is a histamine H3 receptors inhibitor with IC50 of 1.9 μM.
Bicalutamide (Casodex, Cosudex, Calutide, Kalumid) is an androgen receptor (AR) antagonist with IC50 of 0.16 μM.
Bufexamac is a COX inhibitor for IFN-α release with EC50 of 8.9 μM.
Candesartan is an angiotensin II receptor antagonist with IC50 of 0.26 nM.
Carbamazepine (Carbatrol) is a sodium channel blocker with IC50 of 131 μM in rat brain synaptosomes.
Carvedilol is a non-selective beta blocker/alpha-1 blocker with an IC50 of 3.8 μM for inhibition of LDL oxidation.
Celecoxib is a selective COX-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 40 nM.
Cetirizine Dihydrochloride is an antihistamine.
Chlorpheniramine (Chlorpheniramine maleate, Chlorphenamine) is an histamine H1 receptor antagonist with IC50 of 12 nM.
Ciprofibrate is a peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor agonist.
Clomifene citrate (Serophene) is a selective estrogen receptor modulator.

Clomipramine hydrochloride (Anafranil) is a hydrochloride salt of clomipramine which is a serotonin transporter (SERT), norepinephrine transporter (NET) dopamine transporter (DAT) blocker with Ki of 0.14, 54 and 3 nM, respectively.
This agent inhibited cell proliferation of NCI-H727 with IC50 at 9.3 nM.
Cyproheptadine hydrochloride (Periactin) is a hydrochloride salt form of cyproheptadine which is a histamine receptor antagonist for 5-HT2 receptor with IC50 of 0.6 nM.
Diclofenac is a non-selective COX inhibitor with IC50 of 60 and 220 nM for ovine COX-1 and -2, respectively.
Valproic acid sodium salt (Sodium valproate) is a HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 0.4 mM and also inhibits GABA-transaminase or succinic semialdehyde dehydrogenase.
Domperidone(Motilium) is a dopamine blocker and an antidopaminergic reagent.
Etodolac (Lodine) is a COX inhibitor with an IC50 of 53.5 nM.
Flumequine is a synthetic chemotherapeutic antibiotic, inhibiting topoisomerase II with IC50 of 15 μM.
Adrucil (Fluorouracil) is an DNA/RNA synthesis inhibitor, which interrupts nucleotide synthetic by inhibiting thymidylate synthase (TS).
Flutamide (Eulexin) is an oral nonsteroidal antiandrogen agent primarily used to treat prostate cancer.
Gabexate is a serine protease inhibitor with IC50 of 0.19 μM which is used therapeutically in the treatment of pancreatitis and disseminated intravascular coagulation.
Fasudil is a potent inhibitor of ROCK-II, PKA, PKG, PKC, and MLCK with Ki of 0.33 μM, 1.6 μM, 1.6 μM, 3.3 μM and 36 μM, respectively.
Ifosfamide is a nitrogen mustard alkylating agent used in the treatment of cancer.
Irsogladine is an anti-gastric ulcer agent that facilitates gap-junctional intercellular communication through M1 muscarininc acetylcholine receptor binding.
Ketanserin (Vulketan Gel) is specific 5-HT2A serotonin receptor antagonist with a Ki of 2.5 nM for rat and human 5-HT2A.
Ketoconazole inhibits cyclosporine oxidase and testosterone 6 beta-hydroxylase with IC50 of 0.19 mM and 0.22 mM, respectively.
Lamotrigine is a novel anticonvulsant drug for inhibition of 5-HT with IC50 of 240 μM and 474 μM in human platelets and rat brain synaptosomes, respectively.
Lansoprazole is a proton-pump inhibitor (PPI) which prevents the stomach from producing gastric acid.
Letrozole is a third generation inhibitor of aromatase with IC50 of 0.07-20 nM.
Losartan is an angiotensin II receptor antagonist, competes with the binding of angiotensin II to AT1 receptors with IC50 of 20 nM.
Mefenamic acid is a competitive inhibitor of COX-1 and COX-2.
Methazolamide is a carbonic anhydrase inhibitor with Ki of 50 nM, 14 nM and 36 nM for hCA I, hCA II and bCA IV isoforms, respectively
Metoprolol tartrate is a cardioselective β-adrenergic receptor blocker with IC50 of 42 ng/mL.
Mianserin is a psychoactive agent of the tetracyclic antidepressant.
Mitoxantrone is a type II topoisomerase inhibitor with IC50 of 2.0 μM, 0.42 mM for HepG2 and MCF-7/wt cells, respectively
Nevirapine(Viramune) is a non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NNRTI) used to treat HIV-1 infection and AIDS.
Niclosamide can inhibit DNA replication and inhibit STAT with IC50 of 0.7 μM.
Nimesulide is a relatively COX-2 selective inhibitor with IC50 of 26 μM.
Nitrendipine is a dihydropyridine calcium channel blocker with an IC50 of 95 nM.
Ofloxacin is a synthetic broad-spectrum antimicrobial agent.
Omeprazole(Prilosec) is a proton pump inhibitor used in the treatment of dyspepsia.
Ondansetron is a serotonin 5-HT3 receptor antagonist.
Phenacetin is a non-opioid analgesic without anti-inflammatory properties.
Pyrimethamine is a dihydrofolate reductase(DHFR) inhibitor with an IC50 of 15.4 nM.
Quetiapine fumarate(Seroquel) is an atypical antipsychotic used in the treatment of schizophrenia, bipolar I mania, bipolar II depression, bipolar I depression.
Riluzole(Rilutek) is a drug used to treat amyotrophic lateral sclerosis.
Risperidone(Risperdal) is an atypical antipsychotic used to treat schizophrenia.
Rofecoxib (Vioxx) is a COX-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 18 nM.
Imatinib Mesylate is orally bioavailability mesylate salt of Imatinib, which is a multi-target inhibitor of v-Abl, c-Kit and PDGFR with IC50 of 0.6 μM, 0.1 μM and 0.1 μM, respectively.
Levosulpiride is a selective antagonist for D2 dopamine receptors used as an antipsychotic and prokinetic agent.
Ftorafur is a substance being used in the treatment of some types of cancer.

Thalidomide was introduced as a sedative drug,immunomodulatory agent and also is investigated for treating symptoms of many cancers.Thalidomide inhibits an E3 ubiquitin ligase， which is a CRBN-DDB1-Cul4A complex.
Ticlopidine HCl is an P2 receptor inhibitor against ADP-induced platelet aggregation with IC50 of ~2 μM.
Tizanidine is an α2-adrenergic receptor agonist and inhibits neurotransmitter release from CNS noradrenergic neurons.
Trazodone is an antidepressant belonging to the class of serotonin receptor antagonists and reuptake inhibitors for treatment of anxiety disorders.
Triamterene blocks epithelial Na+ channel (ENaC) in a voltage-dependent manner with IC50 of 4.5 μM.
Trimebutine is an agonist of peripheral mu, kappa and delta opiate receptors, used as spasmolytic agent for treatment of both acute and chronic abdominal pain.
Urapidil hydrochloride is a hydrochloride salt form of urapidil which is α1-adrenoceptor antagonist and 5-HT1A receptor agonist with pIC50 of 6.13 and 6.4 respectively.
Venlafaxine is an arylalkanolamine serotonin-norepinephrine reuptake inhibitor (SNRI).
Floxuridine (Fludara) is a prodrugs of floxuridine and an oncology agent with an GI50 of 5.1 μM for the inhibition of MDCK/PEPT1.
Clozapine (Clozaril) is a potent 5-HT1C receptor antagonist with an IC50 of 110 nM for 5-HT-stimulated phosphoinositide hydrolysis.
Amiloride hydrochloride dihydrate is a potent epithelial sodium channel blocker.
Camptothecin (Camptohecine, 20-(S)-Camptothecin, CPT, NSC100880) is a specific inhibitor of DNA topoisomerase I (Topo I) with IC50 of 0.68 μM.
Ritodrine hydrochloride (DU 21220; Miolene; NSC 291565; Pre-Par) is a hydrochloride salt of ritodrine which is a β-2 adrenergic receptor agonist.
Oxcarbazepine inhibits the binding of [3H]BTX to sodium channels with IC50 of 160 μM and also inhibits the influx of 22Na+ into rat brain synaptosomes with IC50 about 100 μM.
Amonafide (NSC-308847) is a selective topoisomerase II inhibitor.
Pefloxacin Mesylate Dihydrate is the third generation of fluoroquinolone class of antibacterials, which inhibits Topoisomerase II activity and DNA replication.
Flupirtine maleate is the salt form of Flupirtine, which is a non-opioid, centrally acting analgesia, muscle relaxation and neuroprotection.
Pravastatin sodium is an HMG-CoA reductase inhibitor against sterol synthesis with IC50 of 5.6 μM.
Clopidogrel (Plavix) is an oral, thienopyridine class antiplatelet agent.
Atorvastatin (Lipitor) is an inhibitor of HMG-CoA reductase used as a cholesterol-lowering medication that blocks the production of cholesterol.
Mizolastine is a histamine H1-receptor antagonist with IC50 of 47 nM used in the treatment of hay fever (seasonal allergic rhinitis), hives and other allergic reactions.

Rilmenidine is a second-generation imidazoline-α2 adrenergic agonist.
Tianeptine is a selective serotonin reuptake enhancer (SSRE) compound used for treating major depressive episodes.
Fulvestrant is an estrogen receptor (ER) antagonist with IC50 of 0.094 nM.
Bosentan is an endothelin (ET) receptors antagonist for ET-A and ET-B with Ki of 4.7 nM and 95 nM, respectively.
Racecadotril is a peripherally acting enkephalinase inhibitor with an IC50 of 4.5 μM
Clofarabine inhibits the enzymatic activities of ribonucleotide reductase (IC50 = 65 nM) and DNA polymerase
Mosapride is a gastroprokinetic agent that acts as a selective 5HT4 agonist.
Valdecoxib is a potent and selective inhibitor of COX-2 with IC50 of 5 nM.
Gefitinib (Iressa, ZD-1839) is an EGFR inhibitor for Tyr1173, Tyr992, Tyr1173 and Tyr992 in the NR6wtEGFR and NR6W cells with IC50 of 37 nM, 37nM, 26 nM and 57 nM, respectively.
Desloratadine is a potent antagonist for human histamine H1 receptor with IC50 of 51 nM.
Abitrexate (Methotrexate) is an antimetabolite and antifolate agent with antineoplastic and immunosuppressant activities.
Esomeprazole magnesium(Nexium) is a proton pump inhibitor to reduce gastric acid secretion.
Desmethyl Erlotinib (CP-473420) is a free base of OSI-420, an active metabolite of Erlotinib (EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 2 nM).
Lapatinib, used in the form of Lapatinib Ditosylate, is a potent EGFR and ErbB2 inhibitor with IC50 of 10.8 and 9.2 nM, respectively.
Sorafenib Tosylate (Bay 43-9006, Nexavar) is a multikinase inhibitor of Raf-1, B-Raf and VEGFR-2 with IC50 of 6 nM, 22 nM and 90 nM, respectively.
Lenalidomide (Revlimid, CC-5013) is a TNF-α secretion inhibitor with IC50 of 13 nM.
Tolfenamic acid is a COX-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.2 μM.
Tropisetron hydrochloride is a selective 5-HT3 receptor antagonist and α7-nicotinic receptor agonist with an IC50 of 70.1 ± 0.9 nM for 5-HT3 receptor.

Chlorprothixene has strong binding affinities to dopamine and histamine receptors, such as D1, D2, D3, D5, H1, 5-HT2, 5-HT6 and 5-HT7, with Ki of 18 nM, 2.96 nM, 4.56 nM, 9 nM, 3.75 nM, 9.4 nM, 3 nM and 5.6 nM, respectively.
Ketoprofen (Actron) is a non-selective NSAID with IC50 of 0.5 μM and 2.33 μM for human recombinant COX-1 and COX-2, respectively.
Flunarizine dihydrochloride is a dihydrochloride salt form which is a calcium channel blocker with a Ki of 68 nM.
Tamoxifen Citrate is an antagonist of the estrogen receptor by competitive inhibition of estrogen binding.
Toremifene Citrate(Fareston, Acapodene) is an oral selective estrogen receptor modulator (SERM) which helps oppose the actions of estrogen in the body.
Nizatidine is a histamine H2-receptor antagonist with and IC50 of 6.7 nM for AChE.
Dasatinib (BMS-354825, Sprycel) is a novel, potent and multi-targeted inhibitor that targets Abl, Src and c-Kit, with IC50 of ＜1 nM, 0.5 nM and 79 nM, respectively.
Tolcapone is a selective, potent and reversible of catechol-O-methyl transferase (COMT) inhibitor with Ki of 30 nM.
Olopatadine hydrochloride(Opatanol) is a histamine blocker and mast cell stabilizer with an IC50 of 559 μM for the release of histamine
Cilnidipine is a calcium channel blocker.
Lacidipine (Lacipil, Motens) is a L-type calcium channel blocker.
Famotidine is a histamine H2–receptor antagonist with IC50 of 0.6 mM, commonly used to treat heartburn, GERD, ulcers, and other digestive conditions.
Pazopanib is a potent and selective multi-targeted receptor tyrosine kinase inhibitor of VEGFR1, VEGFR2, VEGFR3, PDGFR-α/β, and c-Kit.
MDV3100 is an androgen-receptor (AR) antagonist with IC50 of 36 nM.
PLX4032 (Vemurafenib, RG7204, Zelboraf, RO5185426) is a novel and potent inhibitor of B-RafV600E with IC50 of 31 nM.
Olanzapine(Zyprexa) is a high affinity for 5-HT2 serotonin and D2 dopamine receptor antagonist.
Salbutamol (Albuterol) is a short-acting β2-adrenergic receptor agonist with an IC50 of 8.93 µM.
Betaxolol hydrochloride (Betoptic) is a β1 adrenergic receptor blocker with IC50 of 6 μM.
Bethanechol chloride is a selective muscarinic receptor agonist without any effect on nicotinic receptors.
Biperiden is an antiparkinsonian agent of the anticholinergic type.
Dibucaine (Cinchocaine) HCl is a local anesthetics.
Doxazosin mesylate is an alpha-1 adrenergic receptor blocker.
Fenoldopam is a dopamine agonist that causes peripheral vasodilation via stimulation of dopamine 1 (D1) receptors.
Fexofenadine inhibits histamine H1 receptor with IC50 of 246 nM.
Flavoxate is a muscarinic AChR antagonist with IC50 of 12.2 μM.
Fluvoxamine maleate is a selective serotonin (5-HT) reuptake inhibitor (SSRI).
Hexestrol binds to ERα and ERβ with EC50 of 0.07 nM and 0.175 nM, respectively.
Ketotifen fumarate (Zaditor) is a fumaric acid salt of ketotifen which is a H1-antihistamine and mast cell stabilizer.
Loperamide is an opioid-receptor agonist with an ED50 of 0.15 mg/kg.
Nocodazole inhibits Abl, Abl(E255K) and Abl(T315I) with IC50 of 0.21 μM, 0.53 μM and 0.64 μM, respectively.
Naphazoline hydrochloride (Naphcon) is an ocular vasoconstrictor and imidazoline derivative sympathomimetic amine.
Neostigmine bromide(Prostigmin) is a reversible acetylcholinesterase inhibitor.
Orphenadrine citrate is a skeletal muscle relaxant, it acts in the central nervous system to produce its muscle relaxant effects.
Phenoxybenzamine HCl is a non-specific, irreversible alpha antagonist with an IC50 of 550 nM.
Procaine (Novocaine) HCl is an inhibitor of sodium channel, NMDA receptor and nAChR with IC50 of 60 μM, 0.296 mM and 45.5 μM, which is also an inhibitor of 5-HT3 with KD of 1.7 μM.
Proparacaine HCl is a voltage-gated sodium channels antagonist with ED50 of 3.4 mM.
Pyridostigmine Bromide(Mestinon) is a parasympathomimetic and a reversible cholinesterase inhibitor.
Rizatriptan Benzoate(Maxalt) is a 5-HT1 agonist triptan drug for the treatment of migraine headaches.
Scopolamine hydrobromide is a competitive muscarinic acetylcholine receptor with an IC50 of 55.3 ± 4.3 nM.
Sotalol (Betapace) is a non-selective beta blocker and a potassium channel blocker with an IC50 of 43 μM
Sumatriptan succinate is a triptan sulfa drug containing a sulfonamide group for the treatment of migraine headaches.
Hytrin (terazosin) is an alpha-adrenergic blocker used to treat high blood pressure and enlarged prostate.
Tetracaine hydrochloride (Pontocaine) is a hydrochloride salt form of tetracaine which is a potent local anaesthetic and a channel function allosteric inhibitor.
Tropicamide is an anticholinergic and a muscarinic receptor subtype M4-preferring antagonist with IC50 of 8.0 nM.
WY 14643 (Pirinixic Acid) is a potent peroxisome proliferator and activator of PPARα with ED50 of 1.5 μM.
Brompheniramine is a histamine H1 receptors antagonist.
Synephrine HCl (Oxedrine, p-Synephrine) is a sympathomimetic α-adrenergic receptor (AR) agonist.
Acadesine results in accumulation of ZMP, which mimics both activating effects of AMP on AMPK and AMPKK.
Chlorpheniramine (Chlorpheniramine maleate, Chlorphenamine) is an histamine H1 receptor antagonist with IC50 of 12 nM.
Cisatracurium besylate is a nondepolarizing neuromuscular blocking agent, antagonizing the action of acetylcholine by inhibiting neuromuscular transmission.
Topotecan (Hycamtin, NSC 609699) is a topoisomerase I inhibitor for MCF-7 Luc cells and DU-145 Luc cells with IC50 of 13 nM and 2 nM, respectively.
Rimonabant is a selective antagonist of CB1 with IC50 of 13.6 nM and EC50 of 17.3 nM in hCB1 transfected HEK 293 membrane.
Vinblastine inhibits microtubule formation and supresses nAChR activity with IC50 of 8.9 μM.
Ouabain is a selective Na+, K+-ATPase inhibitor, binds to α2 subunit and α3 subunit with Ki of 41 nM and 15 nM, respectively.
Resveratrol is a phytoalexin produced naturally by several plants with anti-cancer, anti-inflammatory, blood-sugar-lowering and other beneficial cardiovascular effects.
Naloxone HCl is an opioid inverse agonist drug used to counter the effects of opiate overdose.
AZD6244 (Selumetinib, ARRY-142886) is highly potent to inhibit MEK1 with IC50 of 14 nM.
